Tools needed to compile:

1) cmake
2) GLUT header files
3) C++ compiler: g++ or Visual C++ Express

On Linux, use the freeglut3-dev package.
On Windows, follow the instruction found at one of the following sites:
     http://user.xmission.com/\~nate/glut.html
     http://www.opengl.org/resources/libraries/glut/

Steps to compile On Linux:
(1) mkdir build
(2) cd build
(3) cmake ../src
(4) make

Steps to compile on Mac (using Xcode)
(1) mkdir build
(2) cd build
(3) cmake -GXcode ../src
(4) open the Xcode project file

Under the "Product" menu, Select "Manage Schemes" to enable only the "gp" target

Steps to compile on Windows:
(1) mkdir build
(2) cd build
(3) cmake ../src
(4) nmake

A binary executable gp[.exe] should be found under the "build" directory


